data.description: Beautiful home with large open floor plan with separate den, living and dining areas that says "Custom Built" in every way! 18' ceilings in living, dining and foyer areas and large double paned E-Glass windows create a "WOW factor" when you walk through the front door. Two gas log fireplaces provide coziness and the 5-station surround sound allows for different genres of music to be played simultaneously inside and outside.  House is wired for alarm system and motion detected flood lights surround exterior. A large master suite is located on one side of home with 2 bedrooms on the other side.  Office with built in 8' glass French doors and 14' ceiling provide a fantastic work area. This room could also be easily converted to a bedroom. 8" wide all-wood flooring throughout the house was just added 4 years ago. Additional custom features include dimmers on all the light switches and closet and pantry lights that turn on when opened. There is a covered outdoor kitchen with sink, minifridge and grill. The main kitchen appliances are custom too! (double oven, thermador and sub zero fridge). This kitchen includes double island  granite surface counters and backsplash that includes two separate sinks with foot-controlled garbage disposals allowing hands-free cooking/cleaning. Also in the kitchen you'll find a built-in mini-bar that can be concealed to look like cabinets, a built-in wine rack and a wine/beverage chiller. House includes a 460 sq ft heated and cooled gameroom/gym that includes a 1/2 bath and is accessible from the backyard or thru the main garage. This room also includes a separate enclosed golf cart shed. You'll enjoy your large master bedroom that has all glass French doors which lead out onto the patio by the pool. The primary bathroom includes a large jacuzzi tub with a separate walk-in shower. The back yard includes a kidney shaped pool with adjoining hot tub which gives a fountain-like overflow which, if desired, can allow entire pool to be heated. This beautiful custom home sits on a 1/2 acre lot that has a long, secluded driveway and is only one of 4 homes on the Cul-de-sac. The twin gas lanterns located on front porch columns.
data.whatILove: We love to entertain, and this home has been perfect for it! It's tall ceilings, and large, multi-glass windows give it a fantastic open feel. The original owner was a chef, so no expense was spared in designing the kitchen. Getting to live on a Cul-de-sac with just three other homes and no thru traffic gives a feeling of seclusion. We've travelled all over the world and just sitting in our own home feels like many of the resorts we've stayed in. The game room was the place where our children's friends wanted to hang out on the weekends (which was fine with us)! Your kids can go from the pool to the gameroom (that includes a 1/2 bath) without walking (all dripping wet) into your main living area. We are building a home on the river just 2 miles away and wish we could just "take this house with us"!
